    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Polystichum oculatum are inflammation, which it reduces due to its high content of flavonoids that inhibit COX-2 enzyme, and asthma, for which it has been shown to have bronchodilatory effects. It also provides relief from arthritis pain by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes, and anxiety, due to its anxiolytic properties that are attributed to its flavonoid content. Moreover, Polystichum oculatum has been found to have a positive impact on diabetes by reducing glucose levels and improving insulin sensitivity, and hypertension by reducing blood pressure through its vasodilatory effects. Additionally, it has been shown to be effective in treating respiratory infections by inhibiting the growth of certain bacteria and viruses, and allergies by reducing histamine release. Furthermore, Polystichum oculatum has been found to promote wound healing by accelerating collagen synthesis and enhancing tissue repair, as well as treating coughs, respiratory issues, skin conditions, eczema, bronchitis, gastrointestinal issues, high blood pressure, stress, and digestive issues.",
