    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Polystichum oculatum are polysaccharides, flavonoids, phenolic acids, terpenoids, and saponins, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. Polysaccharides have been shown to exhibit immunomodulatory and antioxidant activities by stimulating the production of cytokines and scavenging free radicals. Flavonoids, particularly quercetin and kaempferol, have been found to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, as well as the ability to scavenge free radicals. Phenolic acids, including caffeic and ferulic acids, have been reported to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, while terpenoids, such as \u03b2-sitosterol, have been found to have anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects. Saponins, including oleanolic acid and ursolic acid, have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antiviral activities, highlighting the complex and multifaceted nature of Polystichum oculatum's bioactive constituents.",
